,Recommended,259620,7687515,"Posted: 17 November, 2013",all,raixel,"Ok. So it looks like Minecraft in space, spawning a whole lot of U RIPD OFF MINECRAFT posts in the forums. It does look like minecraft. But it is nowhere near a rip off. Its not even remotely the same game. Now dont get me wrong, I love Minecraft and have owned it since late alpha. So another similar-looking game isnt bad in my book.Now for the review.As I said, it looks like Minecraft. Its a procedurally generated 3d block game, where the world/items are different every single time. So big 3d blocks with texures, prodecurally generated huge maps.But thats where the similarities end. Its a space-RPG for starters. And all the quests and stuff are randomly generated, as far as the quest structure, it runs more like Daggerfall (without the horrid bugs). You meet a group of aliens, who give you random quests and rewards thereof. Enemies are ""demons"", really tought things that fly through the clouds. They are the main focus and plot of the game. There are also other alien races. You run around getting quests and items, fighting bad guys, and trying to stop the demon incursion. Simple, really.Its fun and totally worth 6-7$, especially if you like that style of graphics.I just keep on trying to mine thru walls when I see a room I want to get to though..."
