76561198073178003,Recommended,259620,14104305,"Posted: 21 January, 2015",all,Wolodyjowski,"I don't have much time on my counter according to steam but I've played this game about 5 times now, and have yet to get bored of it. I think the negative reviews are a result of people not understanding what type of game this is, as someone else pointed out it's somewhat like doom meets daggerfall (purely in a genre way), the game isn't particularly doom-like, but it is a ""primitive"" fps with old school rpg elements. There is alot of content in this game despite it's small download size and the simplicity of the graphics of course.Overall I recommend this game if you like the genre and style, and want a game that isn't the typical multiplayer nonsense, or AAA bad game with good graphics waste of your time. It's a good way to kill a half hour, or ten or twenty minutes of your free time, and doesn't overdo itself, or take itself too seriously. I just bought another one of ""phr00t""'s games, because I like this one, and I hope you keep on making better games. I feel that this format and the developers game making style could potentially make the perfect old school rpg, or first person roguelike rpg..with a little work and improvement."
